I had to revert some of the changes from the merge with Matt. I think he tried to make it more universal with linux/Mac code and I don't like that. I want it to be Windows Universal. Just my preference.
Now the issue was that A&M had changed the format of the files in Fall 2016 so the OCR result was different so I noticed the pattern and created an algorithm that transforms the text file into the original format and then used the old code again.

Was pointed out by Zubin Shah that the way the program calculates averages is not completely accurate because of stacked classes or classes with small groups of people that have high GPAs so it inflates the GPAs. - Changed the GPA and percentages to use actual numbers from students
Also had two bugs I fixed - The Fall 2017 semester has started using M's in the section numbers which messed things up but that is fixed - I use Fall instead of C now.
